					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">PCM streams suffer from transitional disadvantages when it comes to looping as well. All those special effects have to carry over into the next loop. I also don't completely trust PCM for interactive music for the same reason: I can just simply program a flag check in music data. PCM is more of a polling-style transition, and even then, it has to be sample exact (and you need more PCM files to account for special effects fading away during these transitions).<br /><br />I think of Packy and Marlon when I think of pitch modulation... even if the results are not quite right. Playground 2 and House 4 come to mind, and Unknown Song 9 and 13 also contains pitch modulation that sticks out.</div>

