					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is there a way to read the playback pointer of a given channel into the sample? I'm just trying to think of a way to do a real wave-table synth setup with a series of small waveforms (kinda like the PPG synth), without breaking the output stream of the channel and change the timbre on an internal level instead of a note-by-note basis. Can the DSP generate interrupt for when a channel sample block encounters a 'loop' point?</div>

					
